Did CLG make the comeback?

I honestly didn't think too highly of 100T at the start of the season. Most of the players have been around forever yada yada yada but I didn't know much about their personalities or the spirit of the team and the players.
After watching The Heist:
Pr0lly is an incredibly insightful coach, Aphro is humble, smart and a great in-game leader, Ssumday is massively talented and has a heart of gold, Cody is humble and always hungry to improve, Meteos is proving that he's not just a meme streamer and Ryu is just a rock who's constantly improving in and out of game. All of their personalities really shine through and create a really strong image of a massively talented yet super humble and hungry team.

On top of that they have BY FAR the best looking merch and the best video production the LCS has ever seen. Last but definitely not least, the part that has surprised and impressed me the most and done more than anything else to make 100T one of my absolute favorites is Nadeshot. I don't play CoD, never have and likely never will and I knew nothing of Nade before the start of this season but boy has he impressed me .. He is the complete opposite of the "stereotypical CoD-player". He's passionate, he's energetic, he's funny, he's supportive and humble and most importantly he really, truly cares about his players and the team. He's such a positive and likable personality and seems like a genuinely nice guy despite knowing virtually nothing about league. Huge shoutout to Nade and to the 100T org. Let's finish off this Cinderella story of a first split strong boys - 3, 2 ,1, HUNNIT!
